abstract: The company had until Thursday night to submit the proposals to end a three-year investigation focused on the dominance of its search service.
snippet: The company had until Thursday night to submit the proposals to end a three-year investigation focused on the dominance of its search service.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — European officials said on Friday that Google had submitted proposals aimed at ending a three-year antitrust case focused on its search service, but the offer did not prevent rivals from seeking to prolong its legal entanglements.

headline.main: Google Makes Offer in 3-Year European Antitrust Case
headline.print_headline: Google Makes Offer in 3-Year European Antitrust Case
